articles.title: 'Volcano of Fire' erupts in Central America - New York Post
articles.description: According to data from Global Volcanism Program, the latest eruption cycle of the Fuego Volcano began in 2002, but the recent event is the most significant in several years.
articles.content:
A volcano less than 30 miles outside of Guatemala City is once again erupting, sending ash, gas and rocks down the mountainside, the countrys National Disaster Reduction Commission reports.
